    "body": "Current the panic brings backtraces into `osdk_test_kernel::panic_handler`, not showing panic info (string description), which is hard to know the context (backtraces below the third are useful though).\n\n```rust\nerror: abnormal termination: the program aborted execution\n  --> /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/osdk/deps/test-kernel/src/lib.rs:91:5\n   |\n91 |     abort();\n   |     ^^^^^^^ abnormal termination occurred here\n   |\n   = note: stack backtrace:\n           0: osdk_test_kernel::panic_handler\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/osdk/deps/test-kernel/src/lib.rs:91:5: 91:12\n           1: osdk_test_kernel::__ostd_panic_handler\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/osdk/deps/test-kernel/src/lib.rs:88:1: 88:30\n           2: panic\n               at src/main.rs:28:14: 28:40\n           3: ostd::boot::smp::construct_hw_cpu_id_mapping\n               at /home/zjp/.rustup/toolchains/nightly-2026-04-03-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/lib/rustlib/src/rust/library/core/src/macros/mod.rs:51:21: 51:114\n...\n```\n\nThis problem has been around: https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20the%20program%20aborted%20execution \nSpecifically https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/73 | https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/71 | https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/62 | https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/66 | https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/31",
